        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 6:40PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 640 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Gore Springs, or 14 miles northeast of Grenada, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Spearman, Pittsboro, Benwood, Bounds, Derma, Reid, Loyd, Ellard,
Vardaman, Bruce, Shepherd, Skuna, Tyson, Gums, Retreat, Big Creek,
and Calhoun City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
